ItemÂ 6.
Contracts, Arrangements, Understandings or Relationships With Respect to Securities of the Issuer. 
June 2017 Secondary Offering 
On JuneÂ 15, 2017, the Issuer and Sponsor Stockholders entered into an underwriting agreement (the Â“June 2017 Underwriting
AgreementÂ”) with the underwriter named therein (the Â“June 2017 UnderwriterÂ”). Pursuant to the June 2017 Underwriting Agreement, the Sponsor Stockholders sold in the aggregate 9,650,000 shares of Common Stock to the June
2017 Underwriter at a price of $35.40 per share. The sale of the shares of Common Stock pursuant to the June 2017 Underwriting Agreement closed on JuneÂ 20, 2017. 
References to and descriptions of the June 2017 Underwriting Agreement set forth above in this Item 6 do not purport to be complete and are
qualified in their entirety by reference to the full text of the June 2017 Underwriting Agreement, which has been filed as Exhibit F hereto and incorporated by reference herein. 


Lock-Up Agreement 
In connection with the secondary offering described herein, the Issuer, the IssuerÂ’s executive officers and certain directors and the
Sponsor Stockholders have agreed with the June 2017 Underwriter, subject to specified exceptions, not to offer, pledge or sell any of the shares of Common Stock or securities convertible into or exchangeable for shares of Common Stock, for a period
of 30 days after JuneÂ 15, 2017 except with the prior written consent of the June 2017 Underwriter.  References to and descriptions of
the lock-up agreement set forth above in this Item 6 do not purport to be complete and are qualified in their entirety by reference to the full text of the lock-up
agreement, a form of which has been filed as Exhibit G hereto and incorporated by reference herein.  ItemÂ 6 of the Schedule 13D is
hereby amended by amending and restating the first three paragraphs under the Â“Margin Loan FacilityÂ” section as follows:  HLT
Holdco III LLC, an affiliate of the Sponsor Stockholders (the Â“BorrowerÂ”), has entered into (i)Â a Margin Loan Agreement dated as of JuneÂ 30, 2014 (as amended from time to time, the Â“Loan AgreementÂ”) with
the lenders party thereto (each, a Â“LenderÂ”) and Morgan Stanley Senior Funding, Inc. as administrative agent (the Â“Administrative AgentÂ”) and (ii)Â Pledge and Security Agreements, in each case between one of the
Lenders or its affiliate, as secured party (each, a Â“Secured PartyÂ” and, collectively, the Â“Secured PartiesÂ”) and Borrower, as pledgor (the Â“Borrower Pledge AgreementsÂ”). In addition, HLT Holdco III
LLCÂ’s affiliates, HLT Holdco II LLC, HLT BREH Intl II Holdco LLC, HLT BREH VI Holdco LLC, HLT BREP VI.TE.2 Holdco LLC, HLT A23 Holdco LLC, HLT A23 BREH VI Holdco LLC, HLT Holdco III Prime LLC, HLT BREH Intl II Holdco Prime LLC, HLT BREH VI
Holdco Prime LLC, HLT BREP VI.TE.2 Holdco Prime LLC, HLT A23 Holdco Prime LLC and HLT A23 BREH VI Holdco Prime LLC (each, a Â“GuarantorÂ” and collectively, the Â“GuarantorsÂ”) have each entered into (x)Â with each
Secured Party, a Pledge and Security Agreement (each, a Â“Guarantor Pledge AgreementÂ” and, collectively with the Borrower Pledge Agreements, the Â“Pledge AgreementsÂ”) and (y)Â with the Administrative Agent and the
Lenders, a full recourse Guarantee of the BorrowerÂ’s obligations under the Loan Agreement (each, a Â“GuaranteeÂ” and, collectively with the Loan Agreement and the Pledge Agreements, the Â“Loan DocumentsÂ”). 
As of JuneÂ 20, 2017, the Borrower has borrowed an aggregate of $700,000,000 (not including any interest paid in kind) under the Loan
Agreement. Pursuant to the Pledge Agreements, the BorrowerÂ’s obligations under the Loan Agreement are secured by a pledge of a basket of shares of common stock owned by the Borrower and the Guarantors, initially consisting of shares of common
stock of HLT, the Issuer and Park. As of JuneÂ 20, 2017, the Borrower and the Guarantors have collectively pledged approximately (i) 32.8Â million shares of HLT common stock, (ii) 5.1Â million shares of Issuer common stock and (iii)
16.9Â million shares of Park common stock (collectively, the Â“Pledged SharesÂ”).  The loans under the Loan Agreement
mature on or about JuneÂ 30, 2018. Upon the occurrence of certain events that are customary for these type of loans, the Lenders may exercise their rights to require the Borrower to pre-pay the loan
proceeds, post additional collateral, and the Secured Parties may exercise their rights to foreclose on, and dispose of, the Pledged Shares and other collateral, in each case, in accordance with the Loan Documents. 
